<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-20T10:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-20T10:40:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/3542: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-20T11:00:00-04:40">October 20, 1931—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:21 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>80. Acting Receiver General informs me that he had available this morning
                            for remittance to fiscal agents New York today $160,506.31 to be
                            distributed as follows: interest on all bonds $83,790.20, amortization
                                <pb facs="0244" n="124" xml:id="pg_124"/> on 1922 bonds $70, 138.88,
                            amortization on 1926 bonds $6,577.23, representing a deficit on
                            amortization of 1926 bonds amounting to $77,589.43.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>